  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The model is intended to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A full 13-factor assessment is documented: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The intended use scope — Class II CPB device, adult patients, flow rates 2–6 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–4000 RPM, steady-state hemolysis index as the quantity of interest — is described in the Claim and Requirement nodes referenced below.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-cfd-credible",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-generic-cbp-cfd-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-cbp-piv-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-cbp-hemolysis-bench"
  ],
