    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are appropriately scoped out per the ASME V&V 40-2018 assessment matrix for Model Risk Level 2. The CFD hemolysis model is judged credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in CPB service. The Claim and Requirement nodes (bindsRequirement, bindsClaim) fully specify the intended use scope, patient population, operating envelope, and decision context against which this assessment is made.",
